It appears that the gamepad and joystick dead zone is incorrect.  With a dead zone enabled a bound command to an action map should still receive a value in the range of 0..1 but instead it is something other than 0 (for the current defaults it is about 0.3..1).

sim/actionMap.cpp at line 1510 should read as follows:

```
               if( value > 0 )
                  value = ( value - pNode->deadZoneEnd ) * ( 1.f / ( 1.f - pNode->deadZoneEnd ) );
               else
                  value = ( value - pNode->deadZoneBegin ) * ( 1.f / ( 1.f + pNode->deadZoneBegin ) );
```

making the whole dead zone calculation code block look like this:

```
         if ( pNode->flags & Node::HasDeadZone )
         {
            if ( value >= pNode->deadZoneBegin &&
                 value <= pNode->deadZoneEnd )
               value = 0.0f;
            else
            {
               if( value > 0 )
                  value = ( value - pNode->deadZoneEnd ) * ( 1.f / ( 1.f - pNode->deadZoneEnd ) );
               else
                  value = ( value - pNode->deadZoneBegin ) * ( 1.f / ( 1.f + pNode->deadZoneBegin ) );
            }
         }
```

This should produce the correct 0..1 range when using dead zones, and a much smoother gamepad and joystick experience.

